Package model

Class Appointment

java.lang.Object
model.Appointment
public class Appointment extends Object
Represents an appointment in the application. This class models the necessary attributes and methods required to manage an appointment, including its unique identifier, associated user, customer, and contact details, as well as timing and descriptive information.

      public Appointment(int appointmentID, String title, String description, String location, String type, LocalDateTime startDate, LocalDateTime endDate, int customerID, int userID, int contactID)
      Constructs a fully specified appointment with all details.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - Unique identifier for the appointment.
      title - Title or subject of the appointment.
      description - Detailed description of the appointment.
      location - Location where the appointment takes place.
      type - Type of the appointment, categorizing its purpose.
      startDate - Start date and time of the appointment.
      endDate - End date and time of the appointment.
      customerID - Identifier of the customer involved in the appointment.
      userID - Identifier of the user who manages or oversees the appointment.
      contactID - Identifier of the contact associated with the appointment.
